The paper discusses the use of genetic programming (GP) for empirical modeling, which involves developing mathematical models from experimental data. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG), as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also addresses issues related to computational efficiency and generalization ability, which are relevant to systems and control (cs.SY) and software engineering (cs.SE).
